1
00:00:03,491 --> 00:00:07,141
When we hear about these 
different demigods,

2
00:00:07,154 --> 00:00:13,204
should we think, what is known to us 
is unknown to them?

3
00:00:13,399 --> 00:00:18,059
[Gods in Illusion | Beauty of Krishna Consciousness]

4
00:00:18,481 --> 00:00:21,241
From one point of view, 
like when Guru Mahārāj would say,

5
00:00:21,241 --> 00:00:22,411
“Brahmā, Śuka, Śiva—

6
00:00:22,411 --> 00:00:26,301
they’re aspiring for a drop 
of this divine substance.”

7
00:00:26,301 --> 00:00:29,713
So we’ll see 
certain instances,

8
00:00:29,713 --> 00:00:34,083
where Brahmā is vimohan, 
he is deluded.

9
00:00:34,090 --> 00:00:38,440
But deluded by what? 
Kṛṣṇa, it’s Kṛṣṇa-līlā.

10
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:44,607
It is not conventional māyā.

11
00:00:45,483 --> 00:00:52,873
So one context—we’re seeing him 
as the head of the sampradāya,

12
00:00:52,873 --> 00:00:57,172
another context—we’re talking 
about Brahmā-vimohan.

13
00:00:57,172 --> 00:01:01,961
And this is not 
a simple matter.

14
00:01:02,526 --> 00:01:06,736
No less than Madhvācārya, 
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said,

15
00:01:06,736 --> 00:01:13,496
he eliminated chapter 13 
from the Śrīmad Bhāgavatam.

16
00:01:13,496 --> 00:01:17,728
He couldn’t digest that 
the head of the sampradāya,

17
00:01:17,728 --> 00:01:20,849
in Guru Mahārāj’s terms, 
‘could be seduced’

18
00:01:20,849 --> 00:01:25,219
or Brahmā-vimohan, 
put in illusion.

19
00:01:25,979 --> 00:01:29,850
We see in the 8th Canto 
of Śrīmad Bhāgavatam,

20
00:01:29,850 --> 00:01:33,280
in the pastime
of Mohinī-mūrti

21
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:39,800
that Śiva’s bewildered 
by this divine manifestation.

22
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:44,524
And not to leave it there, 
just while we’re on the subject …

23
00:01:44,531 --> 00:01:48,921
Baladev 
in the brahma-vimohana-līlā …

24
00:01:48,922 --> 00:01:51,792
We’re told, the morning 
that that happened,

25
00:01:51,792 --> 00:01:56,072
that that pastime occurred,
was Baladev’s birthday,

26
00:01:56,251 --> 00:01:58,231
Viśvanāth Cakravartī Ṭ􏰅hākur
said.

27
00:01:58,231 --> 00:02:04,651
So he didn’t go that day,
as Yoga-māyā would have it.

28
00:02:04,972 --> 00:02:07,452
He wasn’t cowherding 
with the rest of the boys.

29
00:02:07,452 --> 00:02:11,512
Yaśodā kept him home, Rohiṇī …
and they had some …

30
00:02:11,512 --> 00:02:13,832
He was the birthday boy!

31
00:02:13,932 --> 00:02:16,427
So the birthday boy 
wasn’t there,

32
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:20,467
when Brahmā stole the cows,
and all of that …

33
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:24,657
So, we’re told, 
a year later …

34
00:02:24,657 --> 00:02:29,617
it’s a year, an Earth year—
a moment in Brahmā- loka,

35
00:02:29,825 --> 00:02:37,395
that there are three levels 
of Yoga-māyic influence over Baladev.

36
00:02:37,453 --> 00:02:44,903
And Viśvanāth makes the point there,
how extraordinary Yoga-māyā is.

37
00:02:45,998 --> 00:02:51,138
So that even Baladev, 
he wasn’t aware that this happened.

38
00:02:51,659 --> 00:02:55,629
A year later, we’re told, a few days 
before it was a year later, He …

39
00:02:55,629 --> 00:02:59,462
He went from the third level 
to the second level

40
00:02:59,462 --> 00:03:02,692
and started making 
certain observations.

41
00:03:02,692 --> 00:03:05,202
Then from the second level 
to the first level,

42
00:03:05,202 --> 00:03:07,252
things were becoming 
more clear,

43
00:03:07,252 --> 00:03:12,502
till it all vanished,
and he realized that …

44
00:03:12,502 --> 00:03:17,495
and marvelled at how 
even he didn’t know,

45
00:03:17,495 --> 00:03:20,495
what Kṛṣṇa had done.

46
00:03:20,495 --> 00:03:22,865
That’s something extraordinary.

47
00:03:22,865 --> 00:03:27,520
ahaṁ vedmi śuko vetti
vyāso vetti na vetti vā 
[Cc: 2.24.313]

48
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:30,370
This is part of the beauty 
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness

49
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:35,720
and reminds us
to be humble.

50
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:41,896
That there is 
no final adjustments
 

51
00:03:41,896 --> 00:03:44,896
in the sense 
of a static understanding

52
00:03:44,896 --> 00:03:49,506
of what’s taking place 
at any given place and time,

53
00:03:49,506 --> 00:03:53,506
especially related to the pastimes 
of Lord and His Divine servitors.

